In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims June as National Caribbean-American Heritage Month. He highlights the contributions and diverse cultures of Americans with Caribbean heritage. The article recognizes the historical significance of Caribbean immigrants seeking better lives and the unfortunate history of slavery. The devastating earthquake in Haiti is also mentioned, with a focus on the support provided by the United States and other Caribbean countries. The article emphasizes the achievements and leadership of Caribbean Americans in various sectors while maintaining their cultural traditions. President Obama calls upon all Americans to celebrate the history and culture of Caribbean Americans through appropriate ceremonies and activities.